## Operators in JavaScript ##

*Arithmetic Operators*

These operators are used for mathematical calculations:

+ : Adds two numbers.
- : Subtracts one number from another.
* : Multiplies two numbers.
/ : Divides one number by another.
% : Returns the remainder of a division.
** : Raises a number to the power of another.

*Increment and Decrement Operators*

These are shorthand for adding or subtracting 1 to/from a variable.

Post-Increment (i++): Returns the current value, then increments.
Pre-Increment (++i): Increments first, then returns the new value.
Post-Decrement (i--): Returns the current value, then decrements.
Pre-Decrement (--i): Decrements first, then returns the new value.

*Assignment Operators*

Used to assign or update values:

= : Assigns a value.
+= : Adds and assigns.
-= : Subtracts and assigns.
*= : Multiplies and assigns.
/= : Divides and assigns.
%= : Modulus and assigns.

*Comparison Operators*

Used to compare two values:

== : Checks if values are equal.
=== : Strictly equal (checks value and type).
!= : Checks if values are not equal.
!== : Strictly not equal.
< : Less than.
> : Greater than.
<= : Less than or equal to.
>= : Greater than or equal to.

*Logical Operators*

These are used for Boolean logic:

&& : Logical AND. Returns true if all conditions are true.
|| : Logical OR. Returns true if any condition is true.
! : Logical NOT. Inverts a condition.
Other Operators
Ternary Operator (? :): A shorthand for if-else.
typeof: Returns the data type of a value.
delete: Removes a property from an object.